abstract: >
  Auracelle Charlie is a single-file browser-based governance wargaming simulation
  instrument developed as a doctoral research tool under the E-AGPO-HT
  (Evans-Accelerated Governance Policy Optimisation — Hierarchical Theory) framework.
  It supports facilitated and autonomous multi-actor governance sessions with
  structured round arcs, role-differentiated deliverable capture, real-time
  governance indicator tracking, MITRE ATT&CK compound shock injection,
  Multi-Agent Reinforcement Learning, LLM-backed agentic Policy Owner and
  Red Team roles via the Anthropic API, Policy Stress-Test Outcome Assessment (PSTOA)
  scoring, and cross-session archive tracking for optimization trajectory analysis.
